{
  "stem": "280.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Talk a little bit about that, because that's unusual.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That's something that Americans aren't used to at all.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we were-- yes, you are right.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Orthodox scene in America is so very different.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it's true, by the sheer fact-- Los Angeles and New York-- I mean, Satu Mare was-- the Jewish population of Satu Mare could-- could fit in two blocks maybe in-- in Brooklyn.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Or-- so everything was under one administration.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The rabbis were paid by-- by-- you paid the tax, every Jew paid the tax.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the rabbis were-- were paid a salary from that administration.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So were the-- the school teachers, we-- we also paid the tuition for the elementary-- even the elementary school wasn't free.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The Jewish school you had to pay a tuition.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Well, they had to-- There was no other means for-- to keep it up, to support it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And-- and although there were several smaller shuls, and they were-- how shall I tell you-- not the rabbis, but the [INAUDIBLE], who was like a judge.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "When you had a-- a problem, questions about kashrut, about, you know, problems, questions about Jewish law, all kinds of situations, you went to that judge-like person, to the [INAUDIBLE], who you presented the problem.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he gave you advice and a decision.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So everybody was paid from-- by-- by that the administration, by that community.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It wasn't like-- like in Los Angeles, you have 100 this small shuls, and each one has their own rabbi, and-- and each rabbi is supported by the members of that.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There-- there-- that wasn't like that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When you say you paid a tax, did you pay the tax to the-- to the secular authorities, to the city authorities?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You paid the-- this was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
